# Cline Rules for Snacks911 Web Application

## Project Overview
- **Framework**: Next.js 16 with TypeScript
- **UI Library**: React 19 with Tailwind CSS
- **Database**: Supabase (PostgreSQL) with RLS
- **State Management**: Zustand
- **AI Integration**: Google Generative AI + Custom AI Orchestrators

## Key Directories
- `/src/app/` - Next.js app router pages
- `/src/components/` - React components
- `/src/lib/` - Utilities, stores, and services
- `/src/core/` - Core business logic (AI, recommendations)
- `/src/ai/` - AI runtime and agents
- `/supabase/` - Database migrations

## Development Rules
1. Always use TypeScript with proper types
2. Follow existing naming conventions (camelCase for functions, PascalCase for components)
3. Use Zustand for state management - check existing stores before creating new ones
4. Database changes must include migrations in `/supabase/migrations/`
5. New components should be in `/src/components/` or feature-specific subdirectories
6. API routes should be in `/src/app/api/`

## Before Making Changes
- Check for existing implementations in `/src/lib/` and `/src/core/`
- Review existing Zustand stores in `/src/lib/*Store.ts`
- Check Supabase schema and RLS policies
- Look at existing AI orchestrators for patterns

## Common Tasks
- Add feature: Component + Store (if needed) + API route (if needed) + Types
- Fix UI: Check component in `/src/components/`, styles in Tailwind/CSS
- Database work: Migration file + Type update + RLS policy
- AI logic: Update stores/orchestrators in `/src/lib/` or `/src/ai/`

## Important Files
- `.env.local` - Environment variables (not in repo)
- `middleware.ts` - Next.js middleware
- `src/lib/supabase.ts` - Supabase client
- `src/core/intents.ts` - AI intent definitions
- `src/lib/cartStore.ts` - Shopping cart state

## Testing & Validation
- Run `npm run dev` to start dev server
- Check console for errors
- Test on mobile (responsive design is important)
- Verify Supabase RLS doesn't block operations
